snippet.textDisplay:
I am a skilled psychologist from Yemen, I once drunk some period blood, thinking it was wine, it made me so poorly that I actually spent the night in a coma, and during the coma, I had the most disturbing nightmares ever:-

1- Well, I know this might sound a bit odd and random, but I have dreamt of Zeus mating with a palm tree and begetting an ant that is capable of crawling on the edge of the Higgs Boson!

2- I once also dreamt of my mitochondria protesting to break free from my organelles , claiming that nature has enslaved them !

3- On that night of a full moon, I dreamt of Professor Noam Chomsky eating books and regurgitating the field of Modern Linguistics!

4- The funniest dream I ever had, was when I had a vision of a Neanderthal swallowing a whole apple, and it played ping-pong with his heart while passing down his oesophagus!

5- The most disgusting dream I ever had, was of a female's menstruation blood turning into jelly and been marketed by an Oompa Loompa as Halloween treats!

I regret not listening to mummy and staying away from "vagina juice", now I have developed a neurological disorder!

Do you guys think that my dreams have any philosophical implications at all?

Given that I've been hearing my neurons conspiring to abandon the dwelling of my skull, things don't seem to be heading in the right direction, ever since!

snippet.textDisplay:
Hello, Russel...


I've been a fan of your comedy for several years now. Your jokes makes me smile, even on the shittiest of days... But, oh boy, have I dun-goofed. I live in Denmark, and so there are rarely any cool people here. I learned just too late that you will be having a show here on Thursday, and all the tickets have sold out.


My soul is crushed. My heart is broken. My dreams are shattered. Why, oh why, dear Lord, must this happen to me? I am but a simple buffoon in search of some laughs, and some goofs, and some gafs.


For now, I will continue to just watch your golden content here on Youtube, and maybe next time you come to Denmark, I'll be more prepared. Please come back soon.


Love, Victoria
